<TITLE> New tax measures to cost NBR Tk 48 crore </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 28 (bdnews24.com)  The government is set to count Tk 48 crore in lost revenues for raising tax-free income ceiling, the National Board of Revenue (NBR) said Thursday. The national coffers will lose Tk 48 crore on the government raising the annual tax-free income threshold to Tk 1.5 lakh from Tk 1.2 lakh, NBR chairman Badiur Rahman told reporters at the finance ministry. "The NBR will lose Tk 48 crore straightway for the increase in the minimum non-taxable income for individuals." Rahman, however, said he was confident of reaching the revenue target of Tk 43,850 crore for the upcoming fiscal year. "Income from undisclosed money will help us," he added. bd
